<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Phoebe Burgess was enjoying the first week of spring on Tuesday. </p>

<p>The 31-year-old shared a number of photos to Instagram in which she sat in the grass at her parents' sprawling Bowral estate. </p>

<p>The former WAG absolutely glowed in a white, off-the-shoulder frock with romantic puffed sleeves and a floral print. </p>

<p>Spring is sprung: Phoebe Burgess (pictured) was enjoying the first week of spring on Tuesday. The 31-year-old shared a number of photos to Instagram in which she sat in the grass at her parents' sprawling Bowral estate</p>

<p>The blonde wore her hair down and straight around her face, on which she wore golden toned makeup with pink lipstick.</p>

<p>Phoebe went without accessories but for a chunky rose gold bangle worn on one wrist. </p>

<p>The budding influencer was gleefully playing with a number of jars and tubes of body lotion which sat in a blue box. </p>

<p>Blooming: The former WAG absolutely glowed in a white, off-the-shoulder frock with romantic puffed sleeves and a floral print</p>

<p>Branches of pink flowers lay at her feet, and Phoebe looked absolutely gleeful as she relaxed on what was an idyllic day. </p>

<p>She later traipsed around the garden, posing atop a stone fence among some green shrubbery as she brandished a hand cream. </p>

<p>The former journalist captioned the promotional post in part: 'The world is just better in colour'. </p>

<p>Just like Europe: Phoebe told fans that sitting in her backyard in Bowral made her think of visiting Provence, a region in southeastern France</p>

<p>She added that sitting in her backyard in Bowral made her think of visiting Provence, a region in southeastern France.   </p>

<p>Phoebe wrote: 'In my backyard, under my favourite blossom, at the start of spring... transporting me to the beauty of the South of France'. </p>

<p>The mother-of-two is currently living with her parents, her daughter Poppy, three, and son Billy, one, in the Southern Highlands of New South Wales.</p>

<p>Holiday in the Highlands: 'In my backyard, under my favourite blossom, at the start of spring... transporting me to the beauty of the South of France' she wrote </p>
